This file contains the OpenPGP (GPG) public keys of BatConf maintainers
who are authorized to sign releases. It is the canonical trust anchor for
verifying BatConf release artifacts and signed git tags.

Verify a download:

    # import every authorized signer's key (once)
    gpg --import KEYS

    # verify a signed tag
    git tag -v vX.Y.Z

    # verify a downloaded artifact against its detached .asc signature
    gpg --verify batconf-X.Y.Z.tar.gz.asc batconf-X.Y.Z.tar.gz

Each entry below is one maintainer: a comment line with their name,
primary key fingerprint, and the dates they are an authorized signer,
followed by the ASCII-armored public key block. Generate your block with:

    gpg --armor --export <YOUR_FINGERPRINT> >> KEYS

See docs/source/devguide.md ("Prerequisites: signing keys") for the full
key generation and maintenance procedure. When a maintainer stops signing
releases, remove their key block from this file; signatures they made
while authorized remain valid.

